title: Triple T Tigers
description: The Bears meet three cool tiger brothers. Grizz wants to be just like the oldest Tiger, TK, but he may not be the best role model.

title: Teddi Bear
description: In an endless junkyard the Bears meet Teddi, a sentient teddy bear.

title: Bears and the Beanstalk
description: The Bears work as short-order cooks in a giant's diner.

title: Unica
description: The Bears join forces with Unica, the ultimate forest protector.

title: The Little Mer-Bear
description: In order to live under the sea the Bears must transform into mermaids.

title: Fiesta Day
description: The Bears party it up with a living piñatas for Fiesta Day. Wanting the festivities to never end, Grizz wishes for it to be Fiesta Day everyday.

title: Sheep Bears
description: The Bears get jobs as sheep herders on an idyllic farm.

title: Pirate Parrot Polly
description: On their quest for hidden treasure, the Bears team up with Polly the Parrot Pirate.

title: Snow Place Like Home
description: When the Bears realize whatever they build with snow comes to life they decide to build the biggest snow party of all time.

title: Panda's Family
description: While exploring a lantern festival, the Bears encounter Panda's long-lost family.

title: High Baby Fashion
description: The Bears enter Panda into a fashion contest, but he's got some fierce competition when Madam Malin and Madeline show up!

title: A Real Crayon
description: The Bears find a mysterious crayon that has the power to make anything they draw become REAL.

title: Hashtag #1 Fan
description: Panda gets kidnapped by a pair of deranged French foxes.

title: Meat House
description: The Bears and their new friend Squatter Otter attempt to live in mysterious house made of meat.

title: Witches
description: The Bears accidentally summon three mysterious witches and have to figure out how to get them back home.

title: Big Trouble Little Babies
description: When they realize they're too small for the rides at an amusement park, the Bears use a magic potion to get bigger.

title: Excalibear
description: On the Bears' visit to a medieval vegetable-village, Grizz starts to believe that he's the rightful king.

title: Baba Yaga House
description: Squatter Otter tries to win Panda's trust and convince the Bears to live in a mysterious house.

title: Modern-ish Stone Age Family
description: The Bears are invited to live with a family of cavemen but things get rocky when the bears teach the family about television.

title: A Gross Worm
description: The Bears help Unica return an endangered alien worm to its home.

title: Bubble Fields
description: The Bears try to prove to Unica that they can be expert bubble-ologists.

title: Bears in the Dark
description: The Bears search for their missing box in a dark and scary cave.

title: The Magical Box
description: After Grizz, Panda and Ice Bear receive a special box, the brothers discover its magical ability to transport them anywhere in the universe.

title: No Land, All Air!
description: The Bears find themselves in a world of dog fighting planes and floating airships.

title: Tooth Fairy Tech
description: In order to earn enough money to buy a house, the Bears work as tooth fairies.

title: Baby Bear Genius
description: Ice Bear receives an invitation to attend a prestigious school for baby geniuses… but Grizz and Panda do not.

title: Back to Our Regular Time Period
description: The Bears find themselves trapped in the wrong time period.

title: Happy Bouncy Fun Town
description: The Bears land in the cheeriest place of all time, but Ice Bear starts to feel out of place.

title: A Tale of Two Ice Bears
description: The Bears accidentally clone Ice Bear and Ice Bear has a hard time adjusting.

title: Dragon Pests
description: The Bears and Squatter Otter crash a couple's swanky pad while they're out of town.

title: Bug City Sleuths
description: To survive in a city inhabited by bugs, the Bears become noir-style detectives.

title: Ice Bear's Pet
description: Ice Bear attempts to keep a giant owl-monster secretly as a pet.

title: Boo-Dunnit
description: When the box goes missing at a haunted mansion, the Bears play detective to help uncover the thief.

title: Bath on the Nile
description: The Bears find themselves in an ancient Egyptian spa, but Grizz refuses to take a bath.
